import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
    sns.barplot(x='country', y='pop', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data = data.dropna(subset=['life_expect'])
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='life_expect', hue='country', kde=True, multiple='stack', palette='bright')
    plt.axvline(data['life_expect'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['life_expect'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="cluster", y="life_expect", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='Cluster', ylabel='Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between cluster and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
